 Some 366 Kenyans tested positive for coronavirus on Sunday even as infections appeared to be reducing with the positivity rate falling to 8.7 per cent. The cases were confirmed from 4,205 samples. The death toll rose to 1,587 after another patient succumbed to the virus on Sunday. In a statement, Health CS Mutahi Kagwe said 432 patients recovered from the disease, raising the number of recoveries to 73,028. From the recoveries, 387 were in the home-based care programme while 45 were discharged from various hospitals. “There are 967 patients admitted in various health facilities countrywide and 6,583 are on the home-based isolation and care. Forty-eight patients are in the intensive care unit, 28 of whom are on ventilator support and 18 on supplemental oxygen,” Kagwe said. Two more patients are under observation. “Another 48 patients are separately on supplemental oxygen out of whom 39 are in the general wards while nine are in the high dependency unit.” All the new cases were Kenyans except 20 foreign nationals. The new cases comprised of 236 men and 130 women with the youngest being a one-year-old infant. 